---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Bedant and the writing project Between Body and Meaning."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="kicker">About</p>
    <h1>Between Body and Meaning</h1>
    <p>
      A personal writing project about medicine, psychology, grief, caregiving,
      and the difficult grace of being present with another person.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-band">
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I am Bedant, a biochemistry and pre-med student interested in the human
        side of care: hospice, rural health, suffering, family caregiving,
        psychological life, and the ways people search for meaning inside
        vulnerability.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is not a portfolio and not a clinic. It is a room for essays,
        fragments, observations, and questions I want to treat with patience.
        Some pieces may lean toward medicine, some toward psychology, some
        toward grief and memory. The center is care.
      </p>
      <p>
        I am especially drawn to moments when clinical language is necessary
        but incomplete. What happens around the diagnosis? What does a caregiver
        notice after everyone else has gone home? How does suffering change a
        family, a body, a faith, a future?
      </p>
      <p class="disclaimer-box">
        This site is for reflective and educational writing only. I do not
        provide medical advice. Any clinical or volunteer-related reflections
        are generalized and de-identified to protect privacy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
